records.addlTxt:
The State files an Amended Information which adds count 5, possess illegally obtained prescription, contrary to Section 450.11(7)(h) of the Wisconsin Statutes.
NO CONTEST pleas entered to count 3, Possess controlled substance (Alprazolam); count 4, possess THC and count 5, possess illegally obtained prescription.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1 and 2. Motion granted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend two (2) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 5 only, commencing on 07-22-16 by 6:00 p.m.;
2) An additional eight (8) days county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 5 only, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
6) Maintain employment;
7) Pay court costs;
8) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
9) provide DNA sample.
The defendant has credit for 1 day, if revoked.
Minutes.
